column5: How was the bird hunting.  I rely on the barter system nowadays. Much more consistent harvests. I give the neighbour perch, and he gives me game. Last night's treat was goose breast, slices thin, tenderized and marinated, then pan seared with a topping of fried onions.   Life is good.
Tee Hee you said breast   Looks good Bruce. Hopefully Sunday is good and you will have lots more perch to barter with
Taste just like a roast beef sandwich. Im hungry now.
